    "body": "In my opinion, I think its best to let it dynamically figure it out (for most use cases). \r\n\r\nThis way, we will not pollute the DHT with misconfigurations (there are currently many dead nodes in there, which slows discovery queries for all live nodes). \r\n\r\nFor most standard use cases, the dynamic adjustment should handle everything fine. I'm not super familiar with exactly what the prysm flags do under the hood. The reason we still have these flags in lighthouse is for more advanced use cases. There can be cases where a network is set up to receive on one socket addr and send on another. In this case, the dynamic adjustment won't work as expected and manual intervention is required. The other use case I mentioned was setting up boot-nodes. \r\n\r\nWe have `--listen-address` which allows you to select the interface to listen on (this might be similar to `--p2p-host-ip`). We support DNS in discovery via the `--enr-address` flag, but this removes dynamic ENR updates and assumes your DNS is contactable. \r\n\r\nOur Discovery tries its best to filter dead/misconfigured nodes from the DHT, but it there still appears to be many misconfigurations in the current medalla DHT. I think we'd have a better DHT if everyone just used dynamic ENR updates. ",
