    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "At the end of the day my objective is to provide a healthy, stable, externally reachable node to support the network.\r\n\r\nI am behind a NAT, but I port forward TCP/UDP 9000 and I can be reached by a mostly static DNS record (it is a dynamic DNS record that auto-updates if it does change, but it hasn't changed in 2+ years lol)\r\n\r\nSo I assume that setting `--enr-address=validator.domain.com --enr-udp-port=9000 --enr-tcp-port=9000` is accurate, and while probably not required or recommended for most users (as dynamic discovery would pick it up eventually), it's a valid configuration?",
